04:22.035 --> 04:25.770
- Hey.
- Hey.

04:25.835 --> 04:28.140
What's up?

04:28.174 --> 04:30.642
Just waiting to talk to Howard.

04:30.676 --> 04:33.982
Can I ask about what?

04:34.016 --> 04:35.485
I'm taking your advice.

04:35.519 --> 04:39.322
I'm, uh, giving the case to HHM.

04:39.357 --> 04:41.325
Why?

04:41.359 --> 04:43.160
The fact that Chuck doesn't want me here

04:43.194 --> 04:45.195
has something to do with it.

04:48.533 --> 04:50.334
I'm so sorry.

04:50.368 --> 04:53.471
Why didn't you just tell me?

04:53.505 --> 04:54.572
I just...

04:54.606 --> 04:58.978
I didn't want you hating your own brother.

05:02.552 --> 05:04.853
How did you find out?

05:04.887 --> 05:06.623
Did Kim tell you?

05:06.657 --> 05:08.961
I figured it out on my own.

05:08.995 --> 05:12.298
It's about time, right?

05:12.333 --> 05:14.634
I brought the sandpiper stuff with me.

05:14.668 --> 05:16.302
It's down in my car.

05:16.337 --> 05:19.139
I figure your guys could do the outreach.

05:19.173 --> 05:21.176
If any of those geezers
don't want to sign with you,

05:21.210 --> 05:22.311
just give me their names.

05:22.346 --> 05:25.149
I'll talk them into it.

05:25.183 --> 05:29.817
You know, Jimmy, I never
wanted it to go this way.

05:29.852 --> 05:31.584
If it had been up to me,
we would have at least...

05:31.619 --> 05:33.652
Howard, I get it.

05:33.687 --> 05:37.659
Your brother's very important to the firm.

05:37.694 --> 05:40.160
Sorry I called you a pig fucker.

05:40.194 --> 05:43.667
Well...

05:43.701 --> 05:46.138
We owe you some money, don't we?

05:46.173 --> 05:51.481
The of-counsel fee...
I think we discussed $20,000.

05:51.515 --> 05:53.983
That and whatever the common-fund proceeds

05:54.018 --> 05:55.985
of sandpiper ultimately adds up to,

05:56.019 --> 05:57.654
you'll receive 20% of that...

05:57.688 --> 06:00.323
Should be a very nice payday
for you when it comes.

06:00.358 --> 06:01.592
Yep.

06:01.626 --> 06:04.431
I've got something for you, too.

06:04.465 --> 06:07.769
Uh, it's a shopping list for Chuck.

06:07.803 --> 06:08.937
I mean, he's doing better,

06:08.972 --> 06:10.608
but he still needs deliveries every day.

06:10.642 --> 06:13.777
I think he'd be more comfortable
with someone else doing it.

06:13.812 --> 06:15.447
I see.

06:15.482 --> 06:16.783
You don't have to do it personally.

06:16.817 --> 06:19.053
It just needs to get done.

06:19.088 --> 06:20.722
It's pretty straightforward.

06:20.756 --> 06:23.794
The ice is a pain in the ass,
but he needs it.

06:23.855 --> 06:26.490
I usually sneak into a motel
and fill a garbage bag,

06:26.522 --> 06:30.388
but you can have
whoever you hire just buy it.

06:30.422 --> 06:32.792
The most important thing is the newspapers.

06:32.826 --> 06:35.127
Uh, The New York Times,
The Wall Street Journal...

06:35.161 --> 06:36.128
They're a must.

06:36.162 --> 06:37.295
There's a newsstand on Eubank

06:37.330 --> 06:39.263
that has both of them at 6:00 A.M.,

06:39.297 --> 06:41.432
which is good 'cause he's an early riser.

06:41.467 --> 06:42.668
The Albuquerque Journal he gets delivered,

06:42.702 --> 06:45.336
but somebody still has to
bring it in for him.

06:45.371 --> 06:48.339
You've been doing all of this every day...

06:48.373 --> 06:50.508
For over a year?

06:52.170 --> 06:54.604
You'll take care of this?

06:54.638 --> 06:55.942
Absolutely.

06:56.036 --> 06:58.003
I'll get it done and done right.

07:02.805 --> 07:05.509
I always liked you, Jimmy.

07:05.544 --> 07:06.612
Remember?

07:06.646 --> 07:09.281
I used to call you "Charlie Hustle."

07:09.315 --> 07:11.752
Yeah, I remember that.

07:23.863 --> 07:27.194
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

07:35.070 --> 07:37.835
That was nice.

07:37.870 --> 07:39.670
You sure you're all right?

07:39.704 --> 07:42.171
It's not a crime to let it out.

07:42.206 --> 07:45.006
There's nothing to let out.
Chuck's a sick man.

07:45.040 --> 07:47.674
That's no excuse.

07:47.708 --> 07:49.610
He's my brother.

07:49.644 --> 07:51.411
He thinks I'm a scumbag.

07:51.445 --> 07:53.580
There's nothing I can do to change that.

07:53.614 --> 07:56.916
What else is there to say?

07:56.950 --> 07:59.583
Wow. That's mature.

07:59.617 --> 08:02.218
Dalai Lama's got nothing on me.

08:14.439 --> 08:20.077
O-64, as in, "oh, to be 64 again!"

08:20.112 --> 08:22.583
O-64.

08:22.617 --> 08:28.257
All right. Next up... We got... N-32.

08:28.791 --> 08:34.261
"N" as in "Nancy... Reagan," a
first lady with a lot of style.

08:34.296 --> 08:36.731
Anybody else seen "Hellcats of the Navy"?

08:36.765 --> 08:40.732
All right. No winners yet?

08:40.767 --> 08:46.736
Okay, here's... B-2,
just like the B-2 bomber,

08:46.770 --> 08:48.204
the stealth...

08:48.239 --> 08:51.206
There's probably one taking off
over at Kirtland right now.

08:51.240 --> 08:55.611
We would never know because it's stealthy.

08:55.646 --> 08:58.577
Still no winners? No?

08:58.612 --> 09:00.077
Here we have...

09:02.349 --> 09:04.985
B-4, another "B." How about that?

09:05.019 --> 09:10.957
As in, "before too long, we're
gonna have another winner."

09:12.191 --> 09:14.727
No? Nobody? Okay.

09:14.761 --> 09:17.726
All right.

09:17.760 --> 09:19.762
And here comes...

09:22.132 --> 09:24.940
Hey, it's our old friend "B."

09:24.975 --> 09:27.311
B-12.

09:29.782 --> 09:33.419
"B," as in, uh...

09:33.453 --> 09:36.754
"B," as in...

09:36.788 --> 09:39.756
"Betrayal"...

09:39.790 --> 09:43.960
Benedict Arnold betrayed The United States.

09:43.994 --> 09:47.464
Still no winners.

09:47.498 --> 09:49.465
No?

09:49.499 --> 09:51.801
Okay.

09:51.835 --> 09:53.302
Here it is.

09:57.204 --> 10:00.005
Oh, what are the odds?

10:00.040 --> 10:02.007
Four B's in a row. That's...

10:04.543 --> 10:07.509
B-7.

10:07.543 --> 10:11.011
"B" as in...

10:11.045 --> 10:16.881
"B" as in..."Brother"... brother.

10:18.950 --> 10:22.085
B-7... "Seven brides for seven brothers."

10:22.119 --> 10:24.252
I'm sure a lot of you have brothers.

10:24.286 --> 10:25.955
It's not like mine, though.

10:25.989 --> 10:27.458
Any winners yet?

10:27.492 --> 10:29.459
Take a... take another look, okay?

10:29.494 --> 10:30.893
I'll wait.

10:30.928 --> 10:32.229
All I'm gonna say is,

10:32.264 --> 10:35.500
if it's another "B,"
could have a real problem here.

10:43.206 --> 10:44.638
And...

10:44.673 --> 10:49.475
Hey, it is another "B."

10:49.510 --> 10:51.812
B-5, as in,

10:51.847 --> 10:56.182
"boy, this 'B' thing is
really starting to tick me off."

10:56.217 --> 10:58.853
"B" as in "battleship."
"B" as in "bourbon."

10:58.887 --> 11:03.689
"B" as in "Belize"...
Beautiful place, so I've heard.

11:03.724 --> 11:05.855
I would love to go there.

11:05.889 --> 11:09.259
But, uh, let's face it...
That's never gonna happen.

11:09.293 --> 11:13.660
None of us is ever leaving
this godforsaken wasteland.

11:17.465 --> 11:19.231
Sorry.

11:19.265 --> 11:23.602
Scratch that. Moving on.

11:25.375 --> 11:27.343
I mean, what is it with this place?

11:27.377 --> 11:30.613
It's... it's like living
inside an easy-bake oven.

11:30.647 --> 11:31.778
I mean, look out that window.

11:31.813 --> 11:34.449
It's... it's like a soulless,

11:34.484 --> 11:37.288
radioactive Georgia Oâ€™Keeffe
hellscape out there,

11:37.322 --> 11:39.789
crawling with coral snakes
and scorpions and...

11:39.824 --> 11:42.292
You ever see the movie
"The Hills Have Eyes"?

11:42.327 --> 11:43.794
It's a documentary!

11:43.829 --> 11:46.131
God forbid your car breaks down...

11:46.165 --> 11:47.699
You have to walk 10 steps.

11:47.734 --> 11:49.703
You got a melanoma the size of a pineapple

11:49.737 --> 11:52.740
where your head used to be.

11:52.775 --> 11:55.042
And so you ask, "why?" Why?

11:55.077 --> 11:57.277
If... if that's how I feel,
why do I live here?

11:57.312 --> 11:59.613
Why?!

11:59.648 --> 12:01.583
Excuse me.

12:01.618 --> 12:02.920
Are you gonna read that number?

12:02.954 --> 12:06.424
Yeah. I'm gonna read your number.

12:06.458 --> 12:09.094
And it's another "B."

12:09.128 --> 12:12.930
It's another frigging "B." Boy, of course.

12:12.965 --> 12:16.270
Why not? Why not?!

12:16.304 --> 12:19.637
And the next number...

12:25.144 --> 12:27.778
Uh, quick question...

12:27.813 --> 12:30.114
Who here knows what a Chicago sunroof is?

12:30.148 --> 12:31.348
Anybody?

12:31.382 --> 12:34.851
You, sir? No? Okay.

12:34.886 --> 12:39.188
True story... uh, back home, uh,
there was this guy named Chet.

12:39.223 --> 12:41.696
Now, Chet was a real asshole.

12:41.731 --> 12:44.201
He might have owed me some money.

12:44.236 --> 12:46.868
He might have slept with my wife...

12:46.903 --> 12:49.707
Before she became my ex-wife.

12:49.741 --> 12:51.543
The details don't matter.

12:51.578 --> 12:55.380
Suffice it to say, I was wronged.

12:55.415 --> 12:57.884
All right, so, one summer evening,

12:57.919 --> 13:01.221
I was out having a few drinks...
One or two, maybe three.

13:01.255 --> 13:03.053
You get the picture?

13:03.087 --> 13:06.655
And, uh, who do I see? Chet.

13:06.690 --> 13:08.992
He drove up, and he double-parked

13:09.026 --> 13:11.994
outside a dairy queen and
went in to get some soft-serve.

13:12.029 --> 13:14.663
Now, Chet drove...
And this will give you an idea

13:14.697 --> 13:17.500
of exactly what kind
of a douchebag this guy was...

13:17.534 --> 13:21.003
Drove a white pearlescent BMW 7 series

13:21.037 --> 13:23.202
with white leather interior.

13:23.237 --> 13:25.872
So, I saw that thing,

13:25.907 --> 13:28.876
and I had... I'd had a few, like I said.

13:28.911 --> 13:32.880
And, uh... I climbed up top,

13:32.914 --> 13:37.553
and I may have...

13:37.588 --> 13:42.327
Defecated, uh, through the sunroof.

13:50.471 --> 13:54.608
Not my finest hour... I'll grant you that.

13:54.642 --> 13:57.111
But that's what a Chicago sunroof is.

13:57.146 --> 14:00.384
Now you know. It's a real thing.

14:00.418 --> 14:04.423
I didn't make it up. I'm not
the first person to do it.

14:04.457 --> 14:07.929
There's a name for it.

14:07.963 --> 14:12.436
Guy wanted some soft-serve...
I gave him some soft-serve.

14:12.471 --> 14:16.778
I did not know that his children
were in the backseat.

14:16.812 --> 14:19.615
There was a level of tint on the windows

14:19.649 --> 14:21.451
that I'll maintain to this day

14:21.485 --> 14:25.420
was not legal
in an Illinois-licensed vehicle.

14:25.455 --> 14:28.590
But somehow, that's on me, I guess.

14:30.157 --> 14:33.959
Who leaves two cub scouts
in a double-parked car

14:33.993 --> 14:36.295
with the engine running?!

14:36.329 --> 14:38.798
Come on.

14:38.833 --> 14:40.935
Now, Chet was connected, see?

14:40.969 --> 14:44.104
Like, uh, Cicero connected.

14:44.138 --> 14:46.942
So, usually, I'd be looking
at malicious mischief,

14:46.976 --> 14:49.611
public intoxication,
disorderly conduct, maybe,

14:49.645 --> 14:54.783
but he's got the D.A.
saying indecent exposure,

14:54.818 --> 14:57.251
calling me a sex offender. What?

14:57.285 --> 15:02.593
One little Chicago sunroof, and
suddenly I'm Charles Manson?!

15:02.627 --> 15:06.096
And that's where it all went off the rails.

15:06.131 --> 15:08.266
I've been paying for it ever since.

15:08.300 --> 15:10.635
That's why I'm here!

15:13.474 --> 15:14.943
I don't...

15:20.521 --> 15:23.655
You know what?

15:23.689 --> 15:26.824
Any of this stuff you want, come get it.

15:26.859 --> 15:31.832
Kitty-cat notebooks for everybody.

16:43.780 --> 16:46.247
- What can I get you?
- Old style.

16:46.281 --> 16:47.380
Make it two.

16:47.415 --> 16:48.748
You got it.

16:50.284 --> 16:52.052
- What happened to Merna?
- Merna?

16:52.086 --> 16:53.253
She's doing all right.

16:53.287 --> 16:54.755
She's my step-mom.

16:54.789 --> 16:56.756
She don't come in much anymore.

16:58.459 --> 17:01.427
Tell her slippin' Jimmy says hello.

17:01.462 --> 17:04.432
- Slippin' Jimmy?
- Yeah, she'll know.

17:04.467 --> 17:06.967
I'll tell her. That'll be $5.50.

17:31.590 --> 17:33.558
Marco...

17:33.593 --> 17:35.894
You gorgeous hunk of a man...

17:37.029 --> 17:41.165
How long will you keep me waiting?

17:41.200 --> 17:44.835
Mnh! Wake up, you fat son of a bitch.

17:44.869 --> 17:46.004
Bought you a beer.

17:48.710 --> 17:51.213
- Jimmy?
- In the flesh.

17:53.317 --> 17:55.351
Hey.

17:55.385 --> 17:57.520
So, I'm not dark enough for you, huh?

17:57.554 --> 18:01.089
No, no. I'm just saying
I don't see any color.

18:01.124 --> 18:03.757
I mean, 10 years in the desert,
you should look like, uh,

18:03.792 --> 18:06.928
Anthony Quinn in "Lawrence of Arabia."

18:06.963 --> 18:09.964
Turks... They paid me a golden treasure!

18:09.999 --> 18:11.833
- Yet I am poor...
- Because I am a...

18:11.867 --> 18:13.669
- River to my people!
- River to my people!

18:13.703 --> 18:16.303
Well, hey, I'm Irish, okay?

18:16.401 --> 18:18.202
I spend my time staying out of the sun.

18:18.238 --> 18:20.174
Speaking of pale sons of bitches,

18:20.236 --> 18:22.203
how's your brother doing?

18:22.238 --> 18:24.040
Chuck's fine.

18:24.074 --> 18:25.375
Still working for him?

18:25.409 --> 18:27.378
Sometimes.

18:29.749 --> 18:33.049
What about you... I mean,
besides falling asleep on a bar

18:33.084 --> 18:35.885
at 4:00 on a Wednesday afternoon?

18:38.088 --> 18:40.024
"Lake Michigan Standpipe"?

18:40.059 --> 18:41.285
- What's that?
- My brother-in-law

18:41.310 --> 18:42.061
owns the company.

18:42.095 --> 18:43.662
Wait. Hold it. You got married?

18:43.696 --> 18:45.163
No, no, no. My... my...
My sister Angie's husband.

18:45.197 --> 18:46.398
Ah.

18:46.432 --> 18:47.733
So, what the hell's a standpipe?

18:47.767 --> 18:49.734
Standpipe... You know what a standpipe is.

18:49.768 --> 18:52.407
- I don't think so.
- Fire department comes.

18:52.442 --> 18:53.909
They stick one end of the hose
